The paper deals with game theory and network creation, which are topics commonly found in the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The paper also discusses the structure and quality of equilibria in the network creation game, which falls under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also introduces a generalized version of the basic network creation game, which involves optimizing communication interests, which could be classified under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The paper also discusses the private costs of peers in equilibria, which could be classified under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the maximum and average distance in the network, which could be classified under the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
